messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
What city is your emergency?
What address?
South 1180 West.
Please come quick.
Okay, tell me that one more time so I know I have it right.
220 South, 1180 West. Utah. Come please.
Okay. I have officers headed over there. Tell me the phone number you're calling from, okay? I need to know what happened.
I don't know... I just have blood everywhere.
Okay. I need you to calm down for a minute. I understand, 220 South, 1180 West. My partner is dispatching somebody. Who is bleeding?
I can't, I can't... You need to hurry!
You need to slow down, calm down, okay? I can't understand you. Talk a little quieter, okay?
My wife, it's my wife!
Take a breath for me, okay? What is your name?
I have officers on the way. I need to have some information from you, okay?
I don't know what happened, she came out of the shower and I heard a pop, there's blood everywhere.
I have officers and paramedics on the way, okay? Can you take a breath? Does she have a gunshot wound to the head?
Yes, I think so.
Okay. Where is the gun right now?
In the bathroom.
Who am I speaking to? What is your name?
My name is Colby.
Okay, Colby. Is she conscious?
No, she's not. There's so much blood.
Where is the blood coming from? Her head?
Yes, from her head.
Is this a house or a trailer park?
It's a house. Across from Trafalgar.
Okay. Is she still breathing?
I... I don't know.
I have an officer outside trying to find you. Can you go outside and find him?
Yes, I'm going.
Go out and get the officer so he can help you, okay? My officer is outside.
Hello? Is that the officer on scene?
Yeah, that's the officer.
